st.header("🚀 What's Next?")

st.info("""
Events tell us WHEN something happens.

But what if an operation takes time?

Example:

Fetch User Data

↓

Wait for Server

↓

Receive Response

This leads us to:

⏳ Asynchronous Programming

⏳ Promises

⏳ Async / Await

which powers modern Full Stack Applications.
""")
# --------------------------------------------------
# MODULE 4 : ASYNCHRONOUS JAVASCRIPT
# --------------------------------------------------

st.title("⏳ Module 4 : Async Programming, Promises & Async/Await")

st.success("""
Learning Outcomes

✅ Understand Synchronous Programming

✅ Understand Asynchronous Programming

✅ Work with setTimeout()

✅ Understand Callbacks

✅ Understand Promises

✅ Use Async Functions

✅ Use Await

✅ Connect Async Programming with Full Stack Applications
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# INTRODUCTION
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣ What is Synchronous Programming?")

st.markdown("""
By default, JavaScript executes code line by line.

Each statement waits for the previous statement to finish.
""")

st.code("""

console.log("Step 1");

console.log("Step 2");

console.log("Step 3");

""", language="javascript")

st.success("""
Output

Step 1

Step 2

Step 3
""")

st.info("""
This is called Synchronous Execution.
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# REAL WORLD ANALOGY
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("2️⃣ Real World Analogy")

st.markdown("""

Imagine standing in a queue:

Person 1

↓

Person 2

↓

Person 3

↓

Person 4

Each person waits for the previous person.

This is Synchronous Processing.
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# THE PROBLEM
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("3️⃣ The Problem")

st.markdown("""
Some operations take time:

🌐 API Requests

📁 File Uploads

🗄 Database Queries

🤖 AI Responses

📍 GPS Location

If JavaScript waits for everything,
the webpage becomes unresponsive.
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# SETTIMEOUT
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("4️⃣ Introducing setTimeout()")

st.code("""

console.log("A");

setTimeout(()=>{

console.log("B");

},3000);

console.log("C");

""", language="javascript")

st.warning("""
Predict the Output before checking below.
""")

with st.expander("Show Output"):

        st.success("""

A

C

B

""")

st.markdown("""
Why?

JavaScript does not wait for setTimeout().
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# VISUALIZATION
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("5️⃣ Execution Flow")

st.markdown("""

```text
A Printed

↓

Timer Started

↓

C Printed

↓

3 Seconds Completed

↓

B Printed

""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# CALLBACK FUNCTIONS
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("6️⃣ Callback Functions")

st.markdown("""
A Callback is a function passed into another function.
""")

st.code("""

function greet(callback){

console.log("Hello");

callback();

}

greet(function(){

console.log("Welcome");

});

""", language="javascript")

st.success("""
Output

Hello

Welcome
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# CALLBACK PROBLEM
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("7️⃣ Callback Hell")

st.markdown("""
Multiple nested callbacks become difficult to read and maintain.
""")

st.code("""

step1(function(){

step2(function(){

step3(function(){

step4(function(){

});

});

});

});

""", language="javascript")

st.error("""
This is known as Callback Hell.
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
PROMISES
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("8️⃣ Promises")

st.markdown("""
Promises provide a cleaner solution.

A Promise represents a future result.
""")

st.code("""

const myPromise =

new Promise(

(resolve,reject)=>{

resolve("Success");

}

);

""", language="javascript")

st.info("""
A Promise can be:

Pending

Fulfilled

Rejected
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# PROMISE STATES
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("9️⃣ Promise Lifecycle")

st.markdown("""

Pending

↓

Fulfilled

OR

Rejected

""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# PROMISE EXAMPLE
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("🔟 Promise Example")

st.code("""

const order =

new Promise(

(resolve,reject)=>{

resolve("Pizza Delivered");

}

);

order.then(

(result)=>{

console.log(result);

}

);

""", language="javascript")

st.success("""
Output

Pizza Delivered
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# REAL WORLD EXAMPLE
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣1️⃣ Food Delivery Example")

st.markdown("""

Order Food

↓

Restaurant Prepares Food

↓

Delivery Partner Picks Up

↓

Food Delivered

↓

Promise Resolved

""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# WHY ASYNC AWAIT?
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣2️⃣ Why Async/Await?")

st.markdown("""
Promises are powerful but can become difficult to manage.

Async/Await makes asynchronous code look like normal code.
""")

st.code("""

async function loadData(){

const result =

await myPromise;

console.log(result);

}

""", language="javascript")

# --------------------------------------------------
# ASYNC FUNCTION
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣3️⃣ Async Function")

st.code("""

async function greet(){

return "Hello";

}

""", language="javascript")

st.info("""
Async functions automatically return a Promise.
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
AWAIT
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣4️⃣ Await Keyword")

st.code("""

const result =

await myPromise;

""", language="javascript")

st.success("""
Await means:

"Wait until the Promise completes."
""")

# --------------------------------------------------
# COMPLETE EXAMPLE
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("1️⃣5️⃣ Complete Async/Await Example")

st.code("""

function getData(){

return new Promise(

(resolve)=>{

setTimeout(()=>{

resolve("Data Loaded");

},3000);

}

);

}

async function load(){

const result =

await getData();

console.log(result);

}

load();

""", language="javascript")

with st.expander("Expected Output"):

    st.success("""

(wait 3 seconds)

Data Loaded

""")

# --------------------------------------------------
ACTIVITY
# --------------------------------------------------

st.header("🎯 Activity")

st.markdown("""
Think of 5 real-world situations where waiting is required.

Examples:

✓ Food Delivery

✓ ATM Withdrawal

✓ File Upload

✓ AI Response

✓ Ticket Booking
""")

